Source: grml2usb
Section: grml
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Homepage: http://grml.org/grml2usb/
Vcs-git: git://git.grml.org/grml2usb.git
Vcs-Browser: http://git.grml.org/?p=grml2usb.git

Package: grml2usb
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, syslinux, python
Description: install grml system to usb device
 This script installs a grml ISO to an USB device to be able to boot from it.
 Make sure you have at least one grml ISO or a running grml system (/live/image)
 available.
